  <h2>Our Mission</h2>
  <p>PropertyManagePro exists to help property managers, HOA board members, condo associations, and real estate investors find the right software for their specific needs. We believe that the best purchasing decision starts with unbiased, expert-driven comparison information.</p>

  <h2>Why Trust Us?</h2>
  <p>Our editorial team has collectively evaluated 40+ property management platforms using a rigorous 22-point methodology. We've helped property managers at associations ranging from 10-unit condos to 10,000-unit managed portfolios select and implement their software stack.</p>
  <p>We maintain strict editorial independence. No software vendor can influence our rankings, reviews, or recommendations. See our <a href="/methodology/">full methodology</a> for details.</p>

  <h2>What We Cover</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>HOA / Community Association Software</strong> — Violations, ARC, reserve studies, meeting management</li>
    <li><strong>Condo Association Software</strong> — Master insurance, common elements, special assessments</li>
    <li><strong>Vacation Rental / STR Software</strong> — Channel management, dynamic pricing, guest communication</li>
    <li><strong>Commercial Property Management</strong> — CAM reconciliation, lease administration, tenant portals</li>
    <li><strong>Student Housing Software</strong> — Academic calendar leases, roommate matching, mass turnover</li>
    <li><strong>Mobile Home Park Software</strong> — Lot rent management, home sales, infrastructure tracking</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Our Team</h2>
  <p>PropertyManagePro reviews are written and curated by a small team of property technology analysts, former property managers, and SaaS product experts. Each review reflects hands-on testing, primary research, and aggregation of verified user feedback from G2, Capterra, and Software Advice.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Have questions, suggestions, or found an error? Contact the editorial team: <a href="mailto:editorial@propertymanagepro.com">editorial@propertymanagepro.com</a></p>
